NAME
       execve - execute a program

SYNOPSIS
       #include <unistd.h>

       int execve(const char *path, char *const argv[], char *const envp[]);

DESCRIPTION
       Replaces the current process image with the ELF located at path.
       All previous mappings except for the kernel half are torn down;
       file descriptors stay open across exec unless O_CLOEXEC is set.

       argv and envp are copied into the new user stack as a standard
       sysv-amd64 frame; argv[0] is conventionally the program name.

RETURN VALUE
       Does not return on success. -1 with errno set on failure.

ERRORS
       ENOENT     no such file
       EACCES     not an executable
       ENOEXEC    not a valid ELF64
       ENOMEM     out of memory while loading segments

SEE ALSO
       fork(2), wait(2)
